info.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 21 at 11:10PM PST until January 22 at 9:00AM PST by NWS Oxnard
info.description: ...WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 AM PST MONDAY... * WHAT...South to southeast winds 20 to 35 mph with gusts 40 to 50 mph. Strongest winds across higher terrain and near the coast. * WHERE...San Luis Obispo County Beaches, San Luis Obispo County Inland Central Coast, Santa Barbara County Central Coast Beaches, Santa Barbara County Inland Central Coast, Santa Barbara County Southwestern Coast, Santa Ynez Mountains Western Range and Santa Ynez Mountains Eastern Range. * WHEN...Until 9 AM PST Monday. * IMPACTS...Gusty winds will blow around unsecured objects and make driving difficult, especially for high profile vehicles. Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result.
info.instruction: Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.
